title: Sports Roundup: Lady Cats sweep Russellville to move into tie for 1st
text:
Sports Roundup: Lady Cats sweep Russellville to move into tie for 1st Posted: October 9, 2015 - 10:57pm LOG CABIN DEMOCRAT 
The Conway Lady Cats celebrated Dig Pink Night on Thursday by moving into a tie for first in 7A/6A Central with a 25-20, 25-15. 25-18 volleybll victory over Russellville. 
Aly Brinkley had 13 kills and four blocks for Conway (22-4, 9-2). Morgan Mourot had 15 assists and two aces. Payton Lindsey had 22 digs. 
Conway (13-1, 11-0) won the JV match, 25-14, 25-20. Holly Stewart had eight kills and Aryn Blumenberg 11 assists. Sydney Hawkins added two aces and Megan Solberg, 20 digs. Marlee Scaife and Ashanti Davis had two blocks each. 
They Lady Cats will host 24 teams from throughout the state Saturday in the Lady Cat Invitational. UCA VOLLEYBALL 
LAKE CHARLES, La. – McNeese State (6-13, 3-3) took a hotly contested, 25-21, 17-25, 23-25, 25-23, 15-12 victory over the University of Central Arkansas (9-10, 5-2) volleyball team. 
On the night, the Sugar Bears got double-doubles from Heather Schnars (22 kills, 20 digs) and Amy South (52 assists, 14 digs), while Meganb Nash and junior Fulani Petties added nine kills each. 
The Sugar Bears return to action on Saturday, taking on Nicholls at noon in Thibodaux. CHS TENNIS 
LITTLE ROCK — The Conway Christian girls finished second to Mount St. Mary and the boyus sixth in the 7A Central tennis tournament Thursday at the Rebsamen Tennis Center. 
The Belles had 19 points to Conway’s seven in the girls division. Little Rock Catholic won the boys title. 
Taylor Lemieux of Conway reached the girls singles quarterfinal. The Lady Cats’ Alexis Rogers and Holly Jones lost tO MSM’S Conley Norris and Tyler Noonan in the girls doubles championship. 
Adam Barnett of Conway reached the quarterfinals of boys singles.
